A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Chief Justice Michael P. Boggs; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Chief Justice Michael P. Boggs has long been recognized by the citizens of this
3 state for the vital role he has played in leadership and his deep personal commitment to the
4 welfare of the people of Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, a native of Waycross, Chief Justice Boggs earned his undergraduate degree in
6 political science and psychology from Georgia Southern College before obtaining his Juris
7 Doctor from the Mercer University School of Law, where he distinguished himself as a
8 member of the Moot Court Board, the ABA/Law School Division moot court competition
9 team, and the Order of Barristers; and
10 WHEREAS, after beginning his legal career in Atlanta, he returned to Waycross to establish
11 a general civil trial practice, focusing on personal injury, domestic relations, and real estate
12 matters while serving concurrently as a county attorney, special assistant attorney general,
13 and counsel to the regional Development Authority; and
14 WHEREAS, in 2000, he was elected to the Georgia General Assembly as a State
15 Representative, where he served with distinction on the Judiciary, Public Safety, and
